cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.SC 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) as it deals with the undecidability and complexity of first-order logic and the use of an SMT solver to solve logical problems. It may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category as it describes the design and implementation of an interactive graphical interface for the SMT solver. Additionally, it could be classified under Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses syntactic manipulation options for interacting with the solver. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible category as SMT solvers are commonly used in AI applications. Finally, it could also be classified under Scientific Computing (cs.SC) as it deals with the use of a solver to solve mathematical problems.
